# WERKSCODE — Project Overview

Public blog and portfolio at **WERKSCODE** — *WERKSCODE works*. Inspire self-employed people (especially in Germany) to learn coding with modern AI tools while running a business.

## Audience & tone

- **Audience**: Non-developer entrepreneurs, craftspeople, small-business owners
- **Tone**: Practical, honest, fun — shopfloor meets software
- **Author voice**: Managing director of a small metal manufacturing company who learned to code on the job

## Stack

- Nuxt 4, Vue 3, TypeScript, pnpm
- shadcn-vue, Tailwind v4
- @nuxt/content (blog + portfolio), @nuxtjs/i18n (en/de)
- Drizzle ORM + PostgreSQL
- Docker + Makefile

## Not this project

Do **not** port patterns from private manufacturing apps:

- No Laravel, Sanctum, RPS/ERP, permissions, or enterprise auth
- No private manufacturing app monorepo conventions

Private manufacturing apps exist locally for author context only. **Never** cite their names, schemas, or internals in committed files, commit messages, code comments, or site copy.

## Public repository

This repo is **public from day one** — write code, comments, commits, and docs as if published today. See [`.cursor/public-repo-standards.md`](../public-repo-standards.md).

## Scope discipline

- Minimal diffs; no over-engineering
- Match conventions in `nuxt.config.ts`, `Makefile`, and existing pages
- UI strings in locale files; routes via `localePath()`; content via `useLocalizedContentPath()`
